            </div>
            <div class="about-us-text centered">
              <h2>Who Are We&nbsp;?</h2>
              <p>
                Obour STEM Maths Club is a student-led club based in Obour STEM
                School. We founded the club with the intention of making a
                difference in a field we deeply admire. Our goal was to create a
                home for both those who are curious to expand their knowledge in
                mathematics and those who might see it as an academic nightmare.
                At Obour STEM Maths Club, math is not just a school subject to
                be studied for exams — it’s a realm of logic and creativity.
                Once you understand it, you’ll discover how fun and impressive
                it can be. That’s why we teach math in a creative, easy, and
                enjoyable way, aiming to reach every mind and uncover the reason
                behind every mathematical law. We believe everyone deserves the
                chance to experience the pleasurable side of math through deep
                understanding. Since day one, we’ve been working hand in hand to
                make math more accessible, more enjoyable, and more human.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-us-image rotate-left">
            <img src="/assets/about-1.jpg" alt="#" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-us-row centered" id="our-mission">
          <div class="about-us-row-content centered">
            <div class="row-indicator">
              <div class="circle"></div>
              <div class="vertical-line"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="about-us-text centered">
              <h2>Our Mission</h2>
              <p>
                1- To create high-quality math resources and make them freely
                accessible to every student, regardless of background or skill
                level. 2- To help students prepare for school exams and Math
                Olympiads in a smart, stress-free, and supportive way. 3- To
                build a strong, inclusive community where students can grow
                together, support one another, and stay motivated throughout
                their math journey. 4- To organize exciting competitions and
                activities that ignite curiosity, build confidence, and show
                students the fun and thrill in solving problems. 5- To make math
                more than just a subject—to turn it into an adventure of logic,
                discovery, and lifelong learning.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-us-image rotate-right">
