        <div class="about-us-row centered" id="our-vision">
          <div class="about-us-row-content centered">
            <div class="row-indicator">
              <div class="circle"></div>
              <div class="vertical-line"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="about-us-text centered">
              <h2>Our Vision</h2>
              <p>
                We envision a generation of students who see mathematics not as
                a source of fear, but as a powerful tool — a language to think
                with, a way to solve problems, and a space for creativity. At
                Obour STEM Maths Club, our vision is to shift how students
                experience math — not just in our school, but across Egypt. We
                believe math should be something to connect with, enjoy, and
                explore deeply, not just study for exams. That's why we're
                building more than just a club, we're building a community.
                Through our active WhatsApp group, students from different
                grades and backgrounds come together to share their ideas,
                support each other, and grow collectively. Everyone contributes,
                learns, and uplifts one another. We also produce student-made
                YouTube content — from tutorials and final revision guides to
                Olympiad preparation and problem-solving walkthroughs, all
                tailored to make math more accessible, engaging, and relatable.
                To keep the spirit of curiosity and challenge alive, we
                regularly organize math competitions and problem-solving events
                that ignite excitement and bring out the best in students. These
                competitions don’t just test knowledge — they build confidence,
                teamwork, and a true love for the subject. Our vision is simple:
                to make math a shared, joyful experience, one that inspires
                confidence, curiosity, and a lifelong appreciation for the
                beauty of logic.
              </p>
